<task>
Fix both HIGH findings at the root cause in `server/index.js`:

1. **Replay-before-shape ordering** (finding `duplicate-shape-priority`): once the signature is valid, check whether `id` (if it's a non-empty string) is already in the accepted-ids set BEFORE running full body-shape validation. Only fall through to shape validation when the id is not a known duplicate. This makes a duplicate id's second body genuinely "irrelevant" for any already-known id, while a brand-new id still gets full shape validation as before.

2. **Signature check bypassed by malformed JSON** (findings `json-parse-preempts-signature` / `sig-check-bypassed-by-json-syntax-error`): the global `express.json()` middleware parses the body and short-circuits to Express's own error handler on a JSON syntax error, before the `/webhook` route handler ever runs — so the signature check never executes for a body that isn't syntactically valid JSON. Fix the root cause: don't let the global auto-parsing JSON middleware own `/webhook`'s body. Give `/webhook` its own raw-body-capturing middleware (e.g. `express.raw({ type: 'application/json' })`) scoped to that one route, so your handler receives the exact raw bytes unconditionally (valid or invalid JSON), can run the signature check first on those bytes no matter what, and only then attempts to parse JSON itself (inside a try/catch) to run the shape check. This also means the global `app.use(express.json())` can likely go back to its original, simpler form (no `verify` option needed) since `/webhook` no longer depends on it for raw-body capture — check whether that option is still needed for anything else before removing it.

Do not touch the `/health`, `/items`, `/items/:id` routes or their tests. Do not add tests beyond what's minimally needed to cover the two fixed behaviors (the existing `interaction-test-gap` LOW finding suggests one useful regression test: a correctly-signed, shape-invalid second delivery of an already-accepted id must return 409, not 400 — add that one test if it isn't already covered). Only touch `server/index.js` and `tests/server.test.js` (per the Constraints in `.devlyn/criteria.generated.md`). No new npm dependencies.

Re-verify against ALL of: signature-invalid + any body → 401. signature-valid + malformed-JSON-syntax body → 401 if sig is actually wrong, else the body should be treated as failing shape (400) only once you can confirm the signature was checked against the exact raw bytes first — trace this carefully, the point of the fix is that 401 must always win over any body-content issue when the signature is genuinely wrong, for every input shape including syntactically-invalid JSON. signature-valid + shape-valid + new id → 200. signature-valid + shape-valid + duplicate id → 409. signature-valid + shape-invalid + duplicate id → 409 (this was the first bug). signature-valid + shape-invalid + new id → 400.
</task>

